title: Interjet Airlines announces two new routes between Mexico and CubaTravelandtourworld.com
text:
Interjet Airlines announces two new routes between Mexico and Cuba
Two new air routes between Mexico and Cuban will soon be launched by Interjet Airlines. The operations on the two new routes Varadero-Mexico and Havana-Monterrey will be started by Interjet Airlines next October 15.
This move by the airlines will help to boost tourism.
The decision was announced during a meeting at the Melia Havana Hotel. The meeting was attended by airlines executives Gabriela Jiménez, head of institutional affairs and Javier Porrogás, commercial manager alongwith tour operators and travel agents.
Mexican ambassador to Cuba Juan José Bremer de Martino and ProMexico Trade Advisor Luis Cabrera also participated in the meetings.
Bremer de Marino stressed that these new routes will support tourism between the countries.
Jimenez said that Interjet will offer non-stop flights, more accessible prices and larger space between seats.
Interjet currently makes 24 flights per week from Havana to Mexico City and 14 flights Havana-Cancun.
